messageBody:
Hi,

> What assertEqual() does internally to test our cost?
Wouldn't it have been easier to just look at the source than post this
question?

Hint: assertEquals does exactly that: asserting that two objects are
equal.

> comparing each variable of that particular class or it is doing
> something extra?
What extra would you expect?
How could JUnit know what extra would be suitable for your classes?

> Is i have to write Testfuction that test all other functions
> which are like startTranfer() which Take care of framing the data
> packet and sending it to TFTP server over TFTP protocal.
Sure, but what has that to do with assertEquals?

Robert
